<div id="tutorial">

<h1><span lang="de" xml:lang="de">Archiv des Beispiels</span> - Tutorial</h1>

<h2>Part I - Adding an Example [for which there's no bibliographical
reference yet]:</h2>

<p>This part of the tutorial explains how to add a new example for
which there is no bibliographical reference in the database yet.
</p>

<h3>1. Adding a Uniform Title</h3>

<ul>

  <li>a.) Navigate to the <span
  class="navigation-uniformtitlecontainer">Uniform Titles</span>
  folder and click the <span
  class="add-content">Add&nbsp;a&nbsp;new&nbsp;Uniform&nbsp;Title</span>
  button at the bottom of the list!</li>

  <li>b.) Fill in the form! (Attention: Some fields are not provided by
  default. Click the button to get them, e.g. <span class="button">Add
  Author</span>.)</li>

  <li>c.) <span class="add-content">Add</span></li>

</ul>

<p>Then you have to enter which edition you want to use. Continue
where you are (at the <span class="tab">Editions</span> tab of the
newly created uniform title):</p>

<h3>2. Adding the Edition</h3>

<ul>

  <li>a.) <span
  class="add-content">Add&nbsp;a&nbsp;new&nbsp;Edition</span>
  <br/>Then you are asked which type of reference you want to
  add. Choose one and click <span class="button">Add</span></li>
  
  <li>b.) Fill in the form (address means the publisher's town)</li>

  <li>c.) <span class="add-content">Add</span> <br/>(After adding you
  will be directed to a detailed view of the newly created
  bibliographical reference. You are able to edit the data via
  the <span class="button">Edit</span> button on the right.)</li>
</ul>

<p>The next step is to add the example:</p>

<h3>3. Adding the example</h3>

<ul>

  <li>a) Go to the <span class="tab">Examples</span> tab of the newly
  created reference.</li>

  <li>b) <span
  class="add-content">Add&nbsp;a&nbsp;new&nbsp;Example</span></li>

  <li>c) Fill in the form! (Feel free to enter several terms separated
  by commas into the Meaning/Denotation field.)</li>

  <li>d) <span class="add-content">Add</span>

  </li>

</ul>

<p><strong>You're done!</strong></p>


<h2>Part II - Adding further Examles [for which there is already a
reference in the bibliography]:</h2>

<p>This part of the tutorial explains how to add examples given that
the bibliographical reference is already in the database.</p>

<h3>Cycle of adding further examples:</h3>

<ul>

  <li>a.) Navigate to the <span
  class="navigation-referatory">Bibliography</span> folder.</li>

  <li>b.) Choose a reference form the list and follow the link!</li>

  <li>c.) Follow the steps from part I 3</li>
</ul>


</div>
